result.execSummary:
This case is being appealed. If the court makes a decision in a case that a party disagrees with, the party may have the right to seek review by a higher court to determine if the trial court's decision was correct. Appeals are most often made after a trial or final decision in a case, but an appeal can also occur before a final decision.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Transcript of Post-Conviction Motion Hearing Held on December 11th, 2020

Defendant Dallas Eugene Robinson, #616258 in court with attorney Cole Daniel Ruby.  Defendant Dallas Eugene Robinson, #616258 in custody.  Mark Adam Fruehauf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
. Attorney Ruby calls Tracy Eichhorn-Hicks. Tracy Eichhorn-Hicks appears by phone. Tracy Eichhorn-Hicks is sworn and testified.  
Court finds defendant has voluntarily waived client attorney privileges.
 Attorney Ruby examines Eichhorn-Hicks. Doesn't remember case, hasn't seen transcripts. Doesn't remember layout of property. Has no independant recollection.
State cross examines. 90 percent of practice is criminal cases. 40 years practicing. Has gone to trial over 100 times, numerous homicide trials.
Court contacts Chance Andrews by Zoom. He refuses to testify.
Att Ruby calls Dallas Robinson- sworn and testifies. Attorney didn't have an investigator. Doesn't remember if attorney talked to him about having Andrews testify. He didn't subpoena Andrews. Spoke to his parents about shooting first, Spoke to girlfriend about 3rd person that night at his house. Had asked grandfather for THC, got money from him instead.
Exhibit 1 Photo of front on house (M-O-R)
Exhibit 2 Aerial view of neighborhood (M-O-R)
Att Ruby continues direct exam.
State cross examines.
Court questions witness. Parked kitty  corner to house, saw victims father at house. Everybody had money to buy THC
Att Ruby redirect- Saw father first, then Teah went to door at Andrew's request. When she got back the drove down the alley and parked at Subway.
State recross
Court questions witness.
Court would prefer briefs in writing. Att Ruby to file by 1/22/21.  State has until 02/12/21 to respond. Rebuttal brief by 2/22/21. Will plan to do written decision.
Proposed Writ of Habeas Corpus & Order for Transport

01:15 PM Attorney Cole Daniel Ruby appeared by phone means for Defendant Dallas Eugene Robinson. Prosecuting Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case.  Court approves Attorney Eichhorn-Hicks appearing by phone or zoom.  DA Fruehauf states that the jail will get the Defendant on December 2, 2020.  Attorney Ruby states that the Defendant is now in quarantine.  Court advises the attorneys to update the Court by end of business November 30th if the hearing can proceed.
